Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.format

Class RecordFormatSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store.format.RecordFormatSelector
  • public class RecordFormatSelector
extends Object
    Selects record format that will be used in a database. Supports selection based on the existing store and given configuration.

    Automatic selection is used by various tools and tests that should pretend being format independent (for example backup).

      • selectForConfig

        @Nonnull
public static RecordFormats selectForConfig​(Config config,
                                            LogProvider logProvider)
        Select configured record format based on available services in class path. Specific format can be specified by GraphDatabaseSettings.record_format property.

        If format is not specified DEFAULT_FORMAT will be used.

        Parameters:
        config - configuration parameters
        logProvider - logging provider
        Returns:
        selected record format
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if requested format not found

      • selectForStore

        @Nullable
public static RecordFormats selectForStore​(DatabaseLayout databaseLayout,
                                           FileSystemAbstraction fs,
                                           PageCache pageCache,
                                           LogProvider logProvider,
                                           PageCacheTracer pageCacheTracer)
        Select record format for the given store directory.

        Note: package private only for testing.

        Parameters:
        databaseLayout - directory with the store
        fs - file system used to access store files
        pageCache - page cache to read store files
        pageCacheTracer - underlying page cache operations tracer.
        Returns:
        record format of the given store or null if DatabaseLayout.metadataStore() file not found or can't be read

      • selectForStoreOrConfig

        @Nonnull
public static RecordFormats selectForStoreOrConfig​(Config config,
                                                   DatabaseLayout databaseLayout,
                                                   FileSystemAbstraction fs,
                                                   PageCache pageCache,
                                                   LogProvider logProvider,
                                                   PageCacheTracer pageCacheTracer)
        Select record format for the given store (if exists) or from the given configuration. If there is no store and record format is not configured than DEFAULT_FORMAT is selected.
        Parameters:
        config - configuration parameters
        databaseLayout - database directory structure
        fs - file system used to access store files
        pageCache - page cache to read store files
        pageCacheTracer - underlying page cache operations tracer.
        Returns:
        record format from the store (if it can be read) or configured record format or DEFAULT_FORMAT
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when configured format is different from the format present in the store

      • isStoreAndConfigFormatsCompatible

        public static boolean isStoreAndConfigFormatsCompatible​(RecordFormats format,
                                                        RecordFormats otherFormat)
        Check if a format is compatible with another format. In case if format is not configured or store does not exist yet - we consider formats as compatible.
        Parameters:
        format - a RecordFormats
        otherFormat - another RecordFormats to compare with.
        Returns:
        true if the two formats are compatible, false otherwise.

      • selectNewestFormat

        @Nonnull
public static RecordFormats selectNewestFormat​(Config config,
                                               DatabaseLayout databaseLayout,
                                               FileSystemAbstraction fs,
                                               PageCache pageCache,
                                               LogProvider logProvider,
                                               PageCacheTracer pageCacheTracer)
        Select explicitly configured record format (via given config) or format from the store. If store does not exist or has old format (RecordFormats.generation()) than this method returns DEFAULT_FORMAT.
        Parameters:
        config - configuration parameters
        databaseLayout - database directory structure
        fs - file system used to access store files
        pageCache - page cache to read store files
        pageCacheTracer - underlying page cache operations tracer.
        Returns:
        record format from the store (if it can be read) or configured record format or DEFAULT_FORMAT
        See Also:
        RecordFormats.generation()

      • findSuccessor

        @Nonnull
public static Optional<RecordFormats> findSuccessor​(@Nonnull
                                                    RecordFormats format)
        Finds which format, if any, succeeded the specified format. Only formats in the same family are considered.
        Parameters:
        format - to find successor to.
        Returns:
        the format with the lowest generation > format.generation, or None if no such format is known.
